#load dataset
(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = keras.datasets.cifar10.load_data()
x_train, x_test = x_train / 255.0, x_test / 255.0  # Normalize
y_train, y_test = keras.utils.to_categorical(y_train, 10), keras.utils.to_categorical(y_test, 10)
In[5]:
#eda
def plot_sample_images():
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 5, figsize=(10, 6))
    fig.suptitle("Sample CIFAR-10 Images", fontsize=14)
    for i, ax in enumerate(axes.flat):
        ax.imshow(x_train[i])
        ax.axis('off')
    plt.show()

plot_sample_images()

# Display class distribution
def plot_class_distribution():
    class_counts = np.sum(y_train, axis=0)
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
    plt.bar(range(10), class_counts, color='skyblue')
    plt.xlabel('Class')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('Class Distribution in CIFAR-10 Training Data')
    plt.show()

plot_class_distribution()

#Experimennt1
#DNNs with 2 hidden layers
def create_dnn_2():
    model = models.Sequential([
        layers.Flatten(input_shape=(32, 32, 3)),
        layers.Dense(512, activation='relu'),
        layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),
        layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')
    ])
    model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model

#Experiment5
#DNN with 2 hidden layers + regularization
def create_dnn_2_2():
    model = models.Sequential([
        layers.Flatten(input_shape=(32, 32, 3)),
        layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.001)),  #L2
        layers.BatchNormalization(),  #normlaizaion
        layers.Dense(256, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.001)),
        layers.BatchNormalization(),
        layers.Dropout(0.5),  #dropout
        layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')
    ])
    model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model

def create_dnn_3_2():

#Experiment1
#CNN with 2 conv/max-pooling layers
def create_cnn_2():
    model = models.Sequential([
        layers.Conv2D(32, (3,3), activation='relu', input_shape=(32, 32, 3)),
        layers.MaxPooling2D((2,2)),
        layers.Conv2D(64, (3,3), activation='relu'),
        layers.MaxPooling2D((2,2)),
        layers.Flatten(),
        layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')
    ])
    model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model

#Experiment3
#CNN with 2 conv/max-pooling layers and different activation functions
def create_cnn_2_1():
    model = models.Sequential([
        layers.Conv2D(32, (3,3), activation='relu', input_shape=(32, 32, 3)),  # ReLU activation
        layers.MaxPooling2D((2,2)),
        layers.Conv2D(64, (3,3), activation='tanh'),  # Tanh activation
        layers.MaxPooling2D((2,2)),
        layers.Flatten(),
        layers.Dense(128, activation='sigmoid'),  # Sigmoid activation
        layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')  # Softmax for classification
    ])
    model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model
In[13]:
#Experiment4
#CNN with 3 conv/max-pooling layers and different activation functions
def create_cnn_3_1():
    model = models.Sequential([
        layers.Conv2D(32, (3,3), activation='relu', input_shape=(32, 32, 3)),  # ReLU activation
        layers.MaxPooling2D((2,2)),
        layers.Conv2D(64, (3,3), activation='tanh'),  # Tanh activation
        layers.MaxPooling2D((2,2)),
        layers.Conv2D(128, (3,3), activation='elu'),  # ELU activation
        layers.MaxPooling2D((2,2)),
        layers.Flatten(),
        layers.Dense(128, activation='selu'),  # SELU activation
        layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')  # Softmax for classification
    ])
    model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model
In[14]:
#Experiment5
#CNN with 2 conv/max-pooling layers + regularization
def create_cnn_2_2():
    model = models.Sequential([
        layers.Conv2D(32, (3,3), activation='relu', input_shape=(32, 32, 3)),
        layers.BatchNormalization(),  # Batch Normalization
        layers.MaxPooling2D((2,2)),
        layers.Conv2D(64, (3,3), activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.001)),  # L2 Regularization
        layers.BatchNormalization(),
        layers.MaxPooling2D((2,2)),
        layers.Flatten(),
        layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        layers.Dropout(0.5),  # Dropout Regularization
        layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')
    ])
    model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model

#Experiment6
#CNN with 3 conv/max-pooling layers + regularization
def create_cnn_3_2():
    model = models.Sequential([
        layers.Conv2D(32, (3,3), activation='relu', input_shape=(32, 32, 3)),
        layers.BatchNormalization(),
        layers.MaxPooling2D((2,2)),
        layers.Conv2D(64, (3,3), activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.001)),
        layers.BatchNormalization(),
        layers.MaxPooling2D((2,2)),
        layers.Conv2D(128, (3,3), activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.001)),
        layers.BatchNormalization(),
        layers.MaxPooling2D((2,2)),
        layers.Flatten(),
        layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
        layers.Dropout(0.5),
        layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')
    ])
    model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model

In[16]:
#train models
def train_and_evaluate(model, name):
    history = model.fit(x_train, y_train, epochs=10, batch_size=64, validation_data=(x_test, y_test), verbose=2)
    test_loss, test_acc = model.evaluate(x_test, y_test, verbose=0)
    print(f"{name} - Test accuracy: {test_acc:.4f}")
    return history

In[17]:
def train_and_evaluate(model, name):
    start_time = time.time()
    history = model.fit(x_train, y_train, epochs=10, batch_size=64, validation_data=(x_test, y_test), verbose=2)
    end_time = time.time()
    test_loss, test_acc = model.evaluate(x_test, y_test, verbose=0)
    print(f"{name} - Test accuracy: {test_acc:.4f} - Time: {end_time - start_time:.2f} seconds")
    print("--------")
    return history

}

histories = {}
for name, model in models_dict.items():
    print(f"Training {name}...")
    histories[name] = train_and_evaluate(model, name)

model_results = []

#result input
experiments = [
    ("DNN-2", 0.5165, 1.3567, 0.4992, 1.4245, 229.67),
    ("DNN-2-1", 0.5203, 1.3429, 0.4765, 1.4640, 244.35),
    ("DNN-2-2", 0.4479, 1.6570, 0.3107, 2.2028, 311.38),
    ("DNN-3", 0.5200, 1.3362, 0.4816, 1.4832, 248.37),
    ("DNN-3-1", 0.5277, 1.3201, 0.4985, 1.4176, 382.05),
    ("DNN-3-2", 0.4785, 1.6099, 0.4390, 1.6817, 307.09),
    ("CNN-2", 0.8008, 0.5705, 0.6998, 0.9384, 290.27),
    ("CNN-2-1", 0.8215, 0.5426, 0.6982, 0.9099, 314.32),
    ("CNN-2-2", 0.7472, 0.7608, 0.7031, 0.9109, 517.70),
    ("CNN-3", 0.8107, 0.5373, 0.7189, 0.8482, 347.91),
    ("CNN-3-1", 0.8451, 0.4404, 0.7053, 0.9967, 864.53),
    ("CNN-3-2", 0.7730, 0.8469, 0.6091, 1.4272, 752.78)
]


for model_name, train_acc, train_loss, val_acc, val_loss, process_time in experiments:
    model_results.append({
        "Model": model_name,
        "Train Accuracy": train_acc,
        "Train Loss": train_loss,
        "Validation Accuracy": val_acc,
        "Validation Loss": val_loss,
        "Processing Time (s)": process_time
    })


df_results = pd.DataFrame(model_results)


print(df_results)

#resuls for each experiment by plot
def plot_experiment_results(histories):
    for name, history in histories.items():
        plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
        plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'], label='Train Accuracy', marker='o')
        plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'], label='Validation Accuracy', marker ='x')
        plt.xlabel('Epochs')
        plt.ylabel('Accuracy')
        plt.title(f'{name} Accuracy')
        plt.legend()
        plt.show()
        
        plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
        plt.plot(history.history['loss'], label='Train Loss', marker='o')
        plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'], label='Validation Loss', marker='x')
        plt.xlabel('Epochs')
        plt.ylabel('Loss')
        plt.title(f'{name} Loss')
        plt.legend()
        plt.show()

plot_experiment_results(histories)
